<br>
Now I'm all for clerics, but how can Verant justify this type of dueling tactic?  It bends every rule there is about casting...I have no chance to interrupt and he has essentially no casting time.  The cleric using this loc casting of cheals about 5 times until I was finally dead.  I asked him about it and he said this was a common tactic all the GMs knew about on the PvP servers.  Is this true?  I've tried loc casting with my eyepatch of Plunder and Chain Bridle but it doesnt work for me.<br>
<br>
